@node history
@title "History"

@{b}-- History@{ub}

Version 1.24 (30.5.2004)

  - added new preferences option "Timeout" to set the timeout for
    playing modules. Note: 1.24 cannot load prefs from older versions,
    please create a new prefs file (it's only very few options anyway :)
    The timeout is in seconds, and 0 means no timeout.

  - playlists, preferences and interfaces now have disjoint version
    numbers

  - updated my snail mail address (postcards pretty please :)

Version 1.23 (26.10.2003)

  - made the upper playlist buttons smaller for better looks

  - added module info feature: get extended information about the
    currently played module by pressing "i"

Version 1.22 (24.10.2003)

  - added alphabetical sort (a-z and z-a) for the playlist, and
    changed some keyboard shortcuts there

  - rewrote the formerly buggy shuffle algorithm

Version 1.21 (18.10.2003)

  - entering an asterisk ('*') in the filerequester for adding modules
    returns all the modules in the current directory and all the
    modules in its subdirectories. Their relative path (relative to
    the current directory) is added and sorted alphabetically.
    Very useful to obtain big playlists (e.g. from CDs containing
    MP3s) effortlessly.

Version 1.2 (8.11.2002)

  - made command composition more flexible

  - changed internal version from 1 to 2 (for playlists, preferences and
    interfaces). That means that this version of EasyPlayer *cannot* read
    those files saved by older versions (1.13 or lower). In the unlikely
    case where anybody has a huge amount of playlists or interfaces files
    that he wouldn't want to produce from scratch again, just contact me.

  - included new email-address (rade@ps.uni-sb.de) and
    new WWW-address (http://www.ps.uni-sb.de/~rade/e.html)

Version 1.13 (3.1.2002)

  - one more bug fixed (couldn't cope with an empty "Console"-setting)

Version 1.12 (3.1.2002)

  - fixed some more bugs

  - much better behaviour in low-memory situations and other even more
    improbable circumstances

Version 1.11 (2.1.2002)

  - fixed some bugs

Version 1.1 (1.1.2002)

  - major internal overhaul, lots of bugfixes

  - added online-help

  - added AppWindow-support

  - added shell pattern matching-support

  - revised the guide, thoroughly

  - compiled with good old EC 3.3a again

Version 1.05 (23.12.2001) - Christmas edition 2

  - removed "Recognizing..." and "Starting..."-status line messages
    again

  - added fallback interface-support

  - revised the guide a lot

Version 1.04 (27.12.2000)

  - added "Recognizing..." and "Starting..."-status line messages

  - added "g"-shortcut: jumps to the module in the playlist which is
    being played or was the last one which has been played (if
    EasyPlayer has been stopped). The same goes for the interfaces list.

  - made playlist handling more intuitive: now the "previous module" and
    "next module"-actions go to the previous and next module relative to
    the *highlighted* module.

Version 1.03 (23.12.2000) - Christmas edition

  - removed several Enforcer-hits that came up when the interfaces-list
    had been emptied

  - added "Be quiet"-option to the preferences-window: forces all
    output from the external player to be redirected to NIL:

  - compiled with CreativE 2.12

Version 1.02 (10.6.2000)

  - now all windows "blocked" by (non-parallel) requesters *are* blocked
    (Mario Cattaneo)

  - compiled with CreativE 2.10ß

Version 1.01 (26.12.1999)

  - bugfix in easyrecognize.e (pattern matching now looks at the
    filename rather than entire path of the module)

Version 1.0 (25.12.1999)

  - revised included interfaces a bit (added "PLEASE_CHANGE_PATH:" as a
    prefix to all paths)

  - revised the guide a little bit more

Version 0.91 (28.9.1999)

  - filter can be toggled by pressing "t"

  - "Interface" definition part renamed to "Invocation", "Format" to
    "Recognition"

  - removed path dependencies from included interface file "EYP.ints"

  - revised the guide a bit

Version 0.9 (25.9.1999)

  - (attempted) first Aminet release
@endnode
